Installation Instructions
*************************

This project is built with Meson and targets GTK4.

Basic Installation
==================

The simplest way to build and install TBO is:

  1. Install the required build dependencies:

       * meson
       * ninja
       * pkg-config
       * gtk4
       * cairo
       * librsvg-2.0
       * gettext (for translations)

  2. Configure the build directory:

       meson setup build

  3. Compile the project:

       meson compile -C build

  4. Run the smoke-test suite:

       meson test -C build --no-rebuild --print-errorlogs --num-processes 1

  5. Install it locally:

       meson install -C build

Running Without Installing
==========================

You can run the uninstalled binary directly from the build directory:

    ./build/tbo

Open the bundled sample comic with:

    ./build/tbo data/tut.tbo

Translations
============

Translations live in the `po/` directory and are built automatically by Meson
when gettext tools are available.

Packaging
=========

The repository currently includes:

  * `archlinux/PKGBUILD` for Arch-based systems
  * `debian/` packaging metadata for Debian-based systems

These packaging files are expected to install the application and desktop files
in the standard system locations so that icons, desktop integration and launch
behavior work correctly on a modern Linux desktop.

Cleaning
========

To remove the build directory and rebuild from scratch, simply delete `build/`
and configure it again:

    rm -rf build
    meson setup build
